One of my regular partners is a mage,and even if the pet pathing problem is fixed,mages are still under powered. VI advertised mages as the second best nukers, and it just isn't so. <br>
 1)The four nukes suggested by Silverblade were not overpowering and seemed reasonable for their levels. They seemed very well thought out and balanced.<br>
<br>
 2)Branamen's fast cast pet idea deserves some discussion.<br>
<br>
 3)Kaledin's Lower Resistance focus item is a great idea!<br>
<br>
 4)I don't really like the idea of wizard nukes doing 40% more damage(gasp!). That could lead to some serious aggro problems,instead,I'd like to see mana costs reduced by 40%.That would let ME decide when the mob took more damage,allowing me to control the aggro myself. Plus,and I know this is a little silly,if the mana costs were reduced I could cast more spells (nukes) making the game more fun for me(and isn't that what it's all about?) And that means that in an XP group I would be able to help out a little on every pull,instead of being caught in the nuke,nuke,med,med cycle.<br>
<br>
<br>
 Dlaren <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udlaren4444.showPublicProfile?language=EN>dlaren4444</A> at: 6/10/02 9:07:41 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 5300<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/10/02 11:22 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> pets and lures</span><hr size=1> One more time: Mages do not need lower resistances, since they bypass resistances entirely with their pets.  The damage a mage does is only partly by spells, the rest is by pets, that's how the class works.  Especially now that the pets don't aggro like they used to, don't wander around, and don't attack mezed targets Mages can use them in and for places that they've never dared to.<br>
<br>
Now that there's no reason not to use a pet in nearly every single instance, the Mage has fine damage output regardless of resistances.  Mages DO NOT need a lure-type spell line in any sense, not through a focus, not through anything.<br>
<br>
What mages DO need is more character and thought put into their summon line, with more utility pets and summons. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usilverbladetheenchanter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silverblade the Enchanter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 432<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/11/02 7:33 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pets and lures</span><hr size=1> Grim,<br>
<br>
How about a summoned weapon that procs a lure say about 50-75hp? lvl 55ish spell?<br>
Point is we need a decent summoned proccing weapon since they nerfed Swords of Runes..you can say what you like but outside of Lavastorm and the Hole, that proc is bloody useless now :/ Should jsut have made it a 30 hp or so mage DD proc on any mob *sigh*<br>
Pets lvls versus mobs means that on most non-Luclin high end  mobs pets nukes/procs wont land at all. Large part of epic pet's damage is from its procs.<br>
<br>
Would that be reasonable? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
